# Note: uv.lock is sometimes committed, but if the user wants a clean .gitignore,
# usually it's better to keep it unless they are building a library. 
# For an app, uv.lock is often committed. I'll leave it out of ignore for now 
# and focus on temp/sensitive files. Actually, I'll include it if they want 
# but usually uv projects commit uv.lock. I'll stick to temp files.

